<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-01 15:40:11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Pharmaceutical Maker Issues Warning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- American Home Products, the world's  
seventh-largest pharmaceutical maker, warned Tuesday that 
second-quarter earnings would fall significantly short of Wall 
Street estimates due to weak sales of products for protecting crops 
and livestock. 
</P>
<P>
	Analysts had been expecting earnings of 41 cents a share for the  
quarter ending June 30, but results will only hit 34 cents, the 
company said. 
</P>
<P>
	Although the announcement was made after the markets closed,  
word leaked out enough to push American Home's stock down $5.62 1/2, 
or by almost 10 percent, to $52 a share on the New York Stock 
Exchange. 
</P>
<P>
	Madison, N.J.-based American Home is best known for its line of  
consumer goods, including Robitussin cough syrup, Advil pain 
reliever and Chap Stick lip balm. 
</P>
<P>
	Despite the lower-than-expected earnings, American Home said its  
top drugs-- Premarin, an estrogen replacement, and rheumatoid 
arthritis drug Enbrel-- are performing well. 
</P>
<P>
	But the company said ``unsatisfactory conditions'' in the  
agricultural and livestock businesses are expected to continue into 
next year, 
</P>
<P>
	``We are obviously disappointed with the performance of our  
agricultural and livestock animal health businesses and are 
concerned about their outlook for the near future,'' said Mr. John 
R. Stafford, chairman and chief executive officer. ``We are 
reviewing strategic alternatives with respect to the agricultural 
product and livestock businesses.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The company has been plagued with thousands of lawsuits over its  
recalled diet drugs, Pondimin, half of the popular fen-phen 
combination, and Redux, as well as its birth control device 
Norplant. 
</P>
<P>
	American Home Products has been among the weaker performing big  
pharmaceutical makers. The company nearly merged with Monsanto Inc. 
last year before the deal was called off in October. 
</P>
<P>
	American Home makes numerous herbicides and insecticides that  
farmers use to protect their crops. But with commodity prices at 
their lowest levels in a decade, farmers are choosing the lowest- 
cost chemicals instead of more popular brand names, American Home 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Agricultural product sales declined 18 percent in the first  
quarter due to lower herbicide sales as wholesalers built 
inventories last year. Agriculture products make up about 16 
percent of the company's sales. 
</P>
<P>
	Demand for the company's animal health medicines has also fallen  
as farmers try to contend with dwindling prices for beef and swine, 
the company said. Animal Health makes up less than 6 percent of 
total sales. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
