<HEADLINE> Pavarotti Sings With Boyzone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MODENA, Italy (AP) -- Luciano Pavarotti performed a duet with  
Irish boy band Boyzone at a charity concert Tuesday for the 
children of Kosovo and Guatemala. 
</P>
<P>
	The show -- whose headliners also included Gloria Estefan, Lionel  
Richie, B.B. King, Mariah Carey and Ricky Martin -- is expected to 
raise $1.1 million. 
</P>
<P>
	Modena is Pavarotti's hometown.  
  	   	
</P>
