<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Injury Sidelines Soccer Star Ronaldo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) -- Ronaldo will miss a pair of  
exhibition games between Brazil and the Netherlands, several 
Brazilian news organizations said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The star forward, who plays for the Italian club Internazionale  
of Milan, gave the national team copies of medical exams done in 
Milan and did not seem optimistic about playing, the Estado news 
agency reported. He missed Inter's game Sunday, a 2-0 loss to 
Bologna that cost the team a spot in next season's UEFA Cup. 
</P>
<P>
	The Brazilian national team plays in Rio on Saturday, with the  
second game in Goiana. 
</P>
<P>
	Ronaldo apparently injured his left thigh May 23 against Udinese  
in the final game of the Italian League season and the injury 
worsened May 27 during the opener of the home-and-home playoff 
against Bologna. 
</P>
<P>
	National team doctor Jose Luis Runco called the injury  
relatively minor and said Ronaldo should be able to join the team 
for the America Cup, South America's championship, which begins 
June 29 in Paraguay. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
