<HEADLINE> Marlins Manager Boles Sidelined </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- Florida Marlins manager John Boles, who had hoped  
to be back in the dugout Tuesday, will remain sidelined until next 
week with a sprained neck. 
</P>
<P>
	Boles has been out since Friday because of the ailment. He also  
missed two games in early May to undergo emergency back surgery. 
</P>
<P>
	Boles came to the ballpark Tuesday but was sent home before the  
game against St. Louis. He'll stay at home the rest of the week 
while Fredi Gonzalez manages the team. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm very disappointed and depressed,'' Boles said. ``I'm just  
not over this thing yet. As much as I'd like to proclaim I am, I 
need a little more time.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Boles will undergo therapy the rest of the week, and he hopes to  
return for Florida's series at home against Baltimore beginning 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Through Monday, the Marlins were 1-5 with Gonzalez as interim  
manager. 
</P>
<P>
	``I came in today expecting to coach third base,'' Gonzalez  
said. ``Bolesy says, `You're managing again,' and I said, `Aw, 
shoot.''' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
