<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Red Sox Give Portugal Time Off </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- Boston Red Sox pitcher Mark Portugal is taking a  
few days off to address personal issues after struggling in his 
most recent start. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think that he had some things on his mind other than  
pitching,'' general manager Dan Duquette said Tuesday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Portugal will meet with management again this week, and Duquette  
expects a resolution by Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Portugal, who signed as a free agent in the offseason, is 3-3  
with a 5.33 ERA in 10 starts. He gave up six runs in three innings 
Monday, but the Red Sox rallied for an 8-7 win over the Detroit 
Tigers. 
</P>
<P>
	After that game, Portugal met with Red Sox manager Jimy  
Williams, then left the clubhouse without speaking to reporters. 
His locker was almost empty. 
</P>
<P>
	On Tuesday, Portugal met with Red Sox management to discuss his  
choices, but Duquette would not specify what was discussed. 
</P>
<P>
	``He has some personal issues that need to be resolved before he  
comes back to work,'' Duquette said. ``He's considering a couple of 
different options.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Although Portugal appeared to injure his left shoulder during  
the second inning, Duquette said Portugal was not injured and would 
not be placed on the disabled list. 
</P>
<P>
	Pat Rapp will start in Portugal's spot on Sunday against the  
Atlanta Braves. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
