<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Cowboys Release Receiver Davis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	IRVING, Texas (AP) -- The Dallas Cowboys on Tuesday released wide  
receiver Billy Davis. 
</P>
<P>
	The signing of wide receiver Raghib Ismail to a seven-year,  
$21.5 million deal in April made Davis largely expendable. 
</P>
<P>
	Last season, his first as a starter, Davis had a career-high 39  
receptions for 691 yards and three touchdowns. He also had 11 
special teams tackles. 
</P>
<P>
	Davis, 26, spent his first three years in Dallas as a special  
teams player. 
</P>
<P>
	He signed with the Cowboys as a rookie free agent out of  
Pittsburgh in 1995. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
