<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Injury Might Sideline Ronaldo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) -- A thigh injury might prevent  
Ronaldo from playing for Brazil in two exhibition games against the 
Netherlands. 
</P>
<P>
	The star striker, who plays for the Italian club Internazionale,  
gave the national team copies of medical exams done in Milan and 
did not seem optimistic about playing, the Estado news agency 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
	The Brazilian national team plays in Rio on Saturday, with the  
second game in Goiana. 
</P>
<P>
	Ronaldo apparently injured his left thigh May 23 in the Italian  
championships against Udinese and the injury worsened during a game 
against Bologna on May 27. 
</P>
<P>
	National team doctor Jose Luis Runco called the injury  
relatively minor and said Ronaldo should be able to join the team 
for the Copa America tournament, which begins June 29 in Paraguay. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
