<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Illinois QB Hurt in Car Wreck </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHAMPAIGN, Ill. (AP) -- Illinois quarterback Kirk Johnson was  
hospitalized in fair condition Tuesday after being injured in a 
one-car accident. 
</P>
<P>
	Johnson, who is slated to share starting duties with Kurt  
Kittner next season, sustained chest and head injuries Monday 
evening as a passenger in a car that crashed on Interstate 74, 10 
miles east of Champaign. He will be a senior next fall. 
</P>
<P>
	The Brentwood, Tenn., native was returning from an Athletes in  
Action weekend convention, Illini coach Ron Turner said. 
</P>
<P>
	In the April spring game, the 6-foot-3, 200-pounder was 13-of-28  
for 115 yards with one interception. 
</P>
<P>
	Johnson, 22, started four games last season for the Illini, who  
finished with a 3-8 record. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
