<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Chancellor Sells Billboard Unit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Chancellor Media Corp. is selling its outdoor  
advertising business to Lamar Advertising Co. for $1.6 billion, 
leaving Chancellor to focus on its sizable radio holdings. 
</P>
<P>
	The cash-and-stock deal will leave Chancellor, soon to be  
renamed AMFM Inc., with a 30 percent stake in Lamar, a leading 
out-of-home advertising company based in Baton Rouge, La. 
Chancellor plans to use some of the proceeds to pay down debt. 
</P>
<P>
	Chancellor's move to get out of outdoor ads comes just days  
after its main rival in the radio business, the Infinity 
Broadcasting subsidiary of CBS Corp., made a move in the opposite 
direction. Last Thursday, Infinity agreed to buy the nation's 
leading outdoor advertising firm, Outdoor Systems, for $6.5 billion 
in stock. 
</P>
<P>
	CBS is hoping that the addition of a major outdoor advertising  
outlet will increase its clout with advertisers, allowing it to 
offer packages of ads spanning network TV, radio, and advertising 
on billboards and public transit systems. 
</P>
<P>
	But Chancellor is going the other way, choosing instead to work  
on its massive radio portfolio of some 465 stations across the 
country. In terms of revenue, Chancellor is the largest U.S. radio 
operator. 
</P>
<P>
	``The agreement enables Chancellor's senior operating management  
team to focus on our industry-leading radio station portfolio,'' 
Chancellor chairman Thomas O. Hicks said in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
	The addition of Chancellor's outdoor business will give Lamar  
some 118,500 advertising display faces, making it a major player in 
the outdoor advertising industry. 
</P>
<P>
	Another major radio company, Clear Channel Communications of San  
Antonio, also has a large presence in outdoor advertising. 
</P>
<P>
	Investors gave the deal a thumbs-up. Lamar's shares jumped  
$2.93 3/4, or 9 percent, to $37.06 1/4 while Chancellor's shares rose 18 3/4 
cents to $51. Both trade on the Nasdaq Stock Market. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
