<HEADLINE> Dow Slips 41 in Early Trading / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices have opened mixed. The Dow Jones  
industrial average was down 41 points in today's early going. 
Advancers on the New York Stock Exchange hold a slim lead over 
decliners. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index was down four points and the S&AMP;P 500  
Index was down three points. 
</P>
<P>
	Wall Street returns from a long weekend with a full slate today.  
</P>
<P>
	On the calendar are several economic reports, including a survey  
of business activity in the manufacturing sector. 
</P>
<P>
	Bond prices have been lower, in anticipation of a strong number.  
</P>
<P>
	Several mergers have also been announced, including deals  
between E-Trade and Telebanc Financial, and AmSouth Bancorp and 
First American. 
</P>
<P>
	Airline shares could receive some extra attention today, on word  
of another round of fare hikes. 
</P>
<P>
	Overseas markets have been mostly higher today.  

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
