<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Panthers Sign Highly Touted Pick </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SUNRISE, Fla. (AP) -- The Florida Panthers have signed highly  
touted right wing Ivan Novoseltsev to a three-year contract, just 
beating a Tuesday deadline to keep him from re-entering the NHL 
draft. 
</P>
<P>
	Financial terms were not disclosed. Novoseltsev, a fourth-round  
pick two years ago, reportedly was seeking a deal matching the 
entry-level cap for 1997 draftees of $925,000 per season. 
</P>
<P>
	If the Panthers and Novoseltsev had not reached agreement by  
midnight Tuesday, the speedy Russian would have become eligible for 
the June 26 draft. 
</P>
<P>
	Novoseltsev, 20, scored 57 goals in 68 games last season for  
Sarnia, finishing second in the Ontario Hockey League by one goal. 
He also had 39 assists and led the OHL with 10 game-winning goals, 
drawing comparisons to high-scoring Panthers wing Pavel Bure. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's a quality prospect,'' Panthers assistant general manager  
Chuck Fletcher said. ``He's a good young player who had a good year 
and can score goals.'' 
</P>
<P>
	However, Fletcher indicated Novoseltsev may need another year of  
seasoning before he's ready to help the Panthers. 
</P>
<P>
	``Any 20-year-old, for that matter, would have a tough time  
making our team with Bure and (Mark) Parrish our top two right 
wingers,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Oleg Kvasha, Radek Dvorak and Marcus Nilson -- none older than 22  
-- also can play the right side. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
