<HEADLINE> Braves Activate Smoltz, Option Chen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- Atlanta Braves right-hander John Smoltz was  
activated from the 15-day disabled list and started Tuesday night 
against the Colorado Rockies. 
</P>
<P>
	Left-hander Bruce Chen was optioned to Triple-A Richmond to make  
room on the roster for Smoltz, who was placed on the DL May 17 with 
an inflamed right elbow. 
</P>
<P>
	Smoltz, who missed two starts, is 5-1 with a 2.59 ERA.  
</P>
<P>
	Chen had a pair of no-decisions and a 4.50 ERA in his two starts  
with the Braves, giving up nine hits and six runs in 12 innings. 
  	   	
</P>
