<HEADLINE> Forrest Sawyer Leaves ABC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Forrest Sawyer, a familiar face on ABC News for  
11 years, has left the network. 
</P>
<P>
	Sawyer left to pursue other opportunities, said his agent,  
Arthur Kaminsky. 
</P>
<P>
	``For 11 years, he was an important part of ABC News,'' network  
spokeswoman Eileen Murphy said Tuesday. ``He made the decision that 
he wants to pursue options elsewhere and we wish him nothing but 
the best.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Sawyer worked as a reporter and substitute anchor on  
``Nightline,'' ``World News Tonight'' and other shows. 
</P>
<P>
	Sawyer's salary may have made him a liability at a network that  
is cutting staff. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
