<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Liberty Media Gets Associated Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Liberty Media Group, a cable programming company  
run by TCI founder John Malone, is buying telecommunications 
provider Associated Group Inc. for $2.8 billion in stock. 
</P>
<P>
	Associated, based in Pittsburgh, founded and owns 41 percent of  
Teligent Inc., which provides phone and Internet access service to 
small and medium-sized companies throughout the United States. 
</P>
<P>
	Associated also owns TruePosition Inc., a company that has  
developed a system for locating wireless phones, and has an 
interest in a Mexican cellular telephone company. 
</P>
<P>
	Liberty has stakes in a number of cable channels, including  
Court TV, BET and Discovery Communications. It also owns nearly 
half of TV Guide. 
</P>
<P>
	Liberty, based in Englewood, Colo., was part of TCI, the huge  
cable company run by Malone and acquired by AT&AMP;T Corp. last year. 
Liberty continues to operate independently under Malone's 
leadership and has its own tracking stock. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
