<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Husband Charged in Neb. Coach Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WAHOO, Neb. (AP) -- A first-degree murder charge was filed today  
against a man accused of killing his wife, a high school teacher 
and coach, and then covering up the crime with a staged car 
accident. 
</P>
<P>
	Conviction would carry a sentence of life in prison or the death  
penalty. 
</P>
<P>
	Mark Schnabel, 42, is accused of killing his 40-year-old wife,  
Sandy Schnabel, a popular volleyball coach and 12-year business 
teacher at Yutan High School. 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. Schnabel's body was found under her smashed and burning  
minivan May 22. 
</P>
<P>
	But authorities said they believe her husband either planned his  
wife's death or beat her in a fit of passion, and then placed her 
under the blazing vehicle to cover up the crime. 
</P>
<P>
	Saunders County Attorney Tom Jaudzemis said he is convinced  
Schnabel set the fire, and the autopsy, which showed the fire was 
the cause of Mrs. Schnabel's death, was a ``big, big factor'' in 
his decision to file a first-degree murder charge. 
</P>
<P>
	First-degree murder requires premeditation. The charge also can  
be filed in killings that occur in the commission of another 
felony, such as arson. 
</P>
<P>
	Schnabel, a landscape designer, was arrested Wednesday at his  
wife's burial service. His attorney, Chuck Forrest, maintains that 
Schnabel is innocent. 
</P>
<P>
	Jaudzemis said the Schnabels had marital and financial troubles  
and Schnabel took out a $200,000 life insurance policy on his wife 
about a year ago. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
