<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> SLOC Officials Shuffle Jobs Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- The Salt Lake Organizing Committee has  
promoted Gordon Crabtree to a job with some responsibilities 
similar to those he had when he first started working for the 
committee. 
</P>
<P>
	The SLOC also announced Tuesday that chief operating officer  
Fraser Bullock has taken over as chief financial officer -- the post 
Crabtree was originally hired for -- as part of the restructuring. 
</P>
<P>
	Crabtree will take over as managing director of finance, the  
SLOC said. He will receive the financial updates of most staff 
members previously reporting to former chief financial officer Mark 
Tanner. 
</P>
<P>
	Crabtree will report directly to Bullock as well as Brett  
Hopkins, SLOC's director of financial planning. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1995, Crabtree, who had served as the state's director of  
finance for 10 years, was hired as the SLOC's chief financial 
officer. He quit two years later shortly after Frank Joklik took 
over the SLOC for former president Tom Welch, who pleaded no 
contest to a spouse abuse charge and resigned. 
</P>
<P>
	Crabtree cited personal reasons for quitting, but later  
acknowledged that subsequent changes after Joklik took over 
prompted his resignation. 
</P>
<P>
	Tanner was hired to replace Crabtree, who continued to work for  
the SLOC as a consultant. Crabtree returned full time in July 1998 
as director of finance, a job with narrower responsibilities than 
his earlier post. 
</P>
<P>
	But Joklik resigned during a house-cleaning of the SLOC after  
the Olympic bribery scandal broke. Mitt Romney took over as 
president in February and brought Bullock with him. 
</P>
<P>
	Last month Tanner announced he was resigning to become chief  
financial officer at Salt Lake-based Mrs. Field's Cookies, citing 
financial reasons. He will make considerably more money and his new 
job is more secure, since it will exist after the 2002 Winter 
Olympics are over. 
</P>
<P>
	Tanner dismissed suggestions he resigned because he had felt  
left out since Romney and Bullock's arrival. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
