<HEADLINE> Paris Bourse To Go Public Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. GALLEN, Switzerland (AP) -- The Paris Bourse is ready to go  
public and plans to do so next year, the chief executive of the 
French exchange said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Dominique Brutin said that in the past two years, the Bourse has  
transformed from a cooperative to a company with shares. ``Now we 
are ready,'' he told reporters at a management symposium here. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's very important to us because when you discuss what is the  
best exchange, what is the most efficient if you are on the market 
it's a good answer, it's the real answer,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	The Paris exchange is one of eight major European stock  
exchanges which have signed a memorandum of understanding to form a 
partnership to create a pan-European bourse. 
</P>
<P>
	Officials from the exchanges have said shares from those  
exchanges should be able to trade on each other's exchanges by the 
end of 2000. 
</P>
<P>
	Brutin said a pan-European alliance should be exclusive but also  
should allow for smaller linkups with other exchanges. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
