<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-01 23:40:06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Saab Recalls 26,000 Cars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DETROIT (AP) -- Saab Cars USA Inc. is recalling 26,000 Saab 9000  
cars to fix a defect that could cause the air bags to malfunction. 
</P>
<P>
	The recall announced Tuesday affects Saab 9000s from model years  
1992 through 1994. The automaker said the covers on the air bag's 
electronic control module, located in the engine compartment, could 
allow moisture to enter and corrode its circuit boards. 
</P>
<P>
	That, in turn, could cause the air bag to malfunction. Saab said  
no accidents or injuries had been reported as a result of the 
defect. 
</P>
<P>
	The '92-93 models were equipped with driver's side air bags  
only, while 1994 models came with driver and passenger-side air 
bags. 
</P>
<P>
	Owners of the affected cars will be notified by mail in July and  
asked to schedule an appointment with their Saab dealer to have the 
parts replaced, if necessary, free of charge. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
