<HEADLINE> Shell Sells Division to World Gas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) -- The Shell Co. of Thailand announced an  
agreement Tuesday to sell its liquefied petroleum gas marketing and 
distributing business to World Gas (Thailand) Co. 
</P>
<P>
	The transaction is expected to be completed in early July and  
will involve the transfer of 30 Shell staff, Shell said. Other 
details were not immediately available. 
</P>
<P>
	The Shell Co. of Thailand is part of the Royal Dutch-Shell Group  
of Companies. World Gas (Thailand) Co. is 49 percent owned by SHV 
of the Netherlands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
