<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Carter Leads NBA All-Rookie Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Vince Carter of the Toronto Raptors and Paul  
Pierce of the Boston Celtics were unanimous choices Tuesday on the 
all-rookie team selected by the 29 NBA coaches. 
</P>
<P>
	Also picked for the team were Sacramento's Jason Williams,  
Vancouver's Mike Bibby and Orlando's Matt Harpring. 
</P>
<P>
	Carter, the rookie of the year, and Pierce received 56 points  
each with Williams getting 55, Bibby 47 and Harpring 35. 
</P>
<P>
	Coaches were asked to pick first and second teams, regardless of  
position, and were not permitted to vote for their own players. 
Points were awarded on a 2-1 basis. 
</P>
<P>
	Chosen for the second team were Houston's Michael Dickerson (33)  
and Cuttino Mobley (26), Orlando's Michael Doleac (30), the Los 
Angeles Clippers' Michael Olowokandi (22) and Golden State's Antawn 
Jamison (21). 
</P>
<P>
	Carter and Pierce received the maximum 28 first-team votes.  
Williams was named on 27 first-team ballots, Bibby 19 and Harpring 
10. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
